The President expresses deep sadness over the murder of David Kato, who was a courageous advocate against hate in Uganda. The United States mourns his death and reaffirms its commitment to his work. The President also highlights the ongoing discrimination and violence faced by LGBT individuals globally, citing the recent murders of five LGBT members in Honduras. The President calls on the governments of Uganda and Honduras to investigate these killings and bring the perpetrators to justice. He emphasizes that LGBT rights are human rights and pledges continued support for human rights and assistance for LGBT individuals worldwide. The President recognizes the risks faced by leaders like David Kato and shares their dedication to promoting freedom, fairness, and equality for all.